lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2291:"<p><a href="http://wordcampbirmingham.org/"><img class="alignright size-full wp-image-1763" title="WordCamp Birmingham 2009" src="http://dougal.gunters.org/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2009/09/wcbhm09.jpg" alt="WordCamp Birmingham 2009" width="170" height="105" /></a>In a short while, I&#8217;ll be leaving Atlanta, and heading west to Alabama for <a href="http://wordcampbirmingham.org/">WordCamp Birmingham 2009</a>. I&#8217;m giving a presentation on Saturday morning about <a href="http://wordcampbirmingham.org/schedule/detail/#pluginintro">Jumping Into WordPress Plugin Programming</a>. Of course, my presentation still isn&#8217;t done, so I&#8217;ll be burning the midnight oil tonight, finishing up my notes, gathering up my bookmarks, and turning it all into a slideshow. Unfortunately, my presentation is in the first slot of the morning. Fortunately, once that&#8217;s over with (for better or worse), I can enjoy the rest of WordCamp relatively stress-free.</p>\n<p>Mainly, I&#8217;m looking forward to talking to people, both the people I&#8217;ve met before, like Mitch Canter of <a href="http://www.studionashvegas.com/">StudioNashvegas</a>, and those I haven&#8217;t, like <a href="http://ma.tt/">Matt Mullenweg</a> of&#8230;everything. If you see me wandering around, feel free to introduce yourself. I might be brain-dead from lack of sleep, and not the best conversationalist, but I&#8217;m usually more than happy to talk about WordPress, programming, or other general geekery. <img src="http://dougal.gunters.org/wordpress/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" class="wp-smiley" /> </p>\n\n\n<p>Related posts:<ol><li><a href="http://dougal.gunters.org/blog/2008/10/01/back-from-wordcamp-birmingham-2008" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link: Back from WordCamp Birmingham 2008">Back from WordCamp Birmingham 2008</a></li><li><a href="http://dougal.gunters.org/blog/2008/09/04/wordcamp-birmingham"